  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are formally assessed; seven factors achieve levels marginally below required thresholds, and six factors are scoped-out with documented rationale citing the absence of physiologically equivalent in-vitro test data at MRL 5. The borderline shortfalls across multiple assessed factors collectively justify a Not-accepted decision. No offset rationale is claimed; the rejection reflects the structured evidence of documented gaps.",
