      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/cou2/numerical-code-verification",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Code verification acceptance criteria — MRL 5",
        "description": "Manufactured-solution convergence tests must demonstrate second-order spatial accuracy for all transport equations used in the hemolysis sub-model; results must be documented in a verification report traceable to the regulatory submission."
      },
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy tests using the method of manufactured solutions confirm second-order convergence for momentum and continuity equations. However, the power-law hemolysis damage accumulation sub-model has been verified only against reference solutions from the literature rather than through an independent manufactured-solution test, yielding achieved level 3 against the required level 4. The shortfall is marginal but not offset by any compensating evidence."
    },
    {
