      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/cou2/discretization-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — MRL 5",
        "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be computed on at least three systematically refined meshes with a refinement ratio ≥1.3; GCI for hemolysis index QoI must be below 5% on the finest mesh; Richardson extrapolation estimate must be reported."
      },
      "rationale": "GCI study was conducted on three meshes (4.2 M, 11.7 M, and 29.4 M cells; refinement ratio 1.41). GCI on the finest mesh is 7.3% for the hemolysis index QoI, exceeding the 5% threshold. Richardson extrapolation was performed and reported. The achieved level 3 falls one gradation below the required level 4 because the GCI threshold is not met on the finest production mesh."
    },
    {
