        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria — MRL 5",
        "description": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, hematocrit) must be measured with calibrated instruments traceable to NIST standards; uncertainty bounds on each boundary condition must be reported and propagated into CFD inputs."
      },
      "rationale": "All five flow-speed operating points were tested using a calibrated Coriolis flow meter (±0.5% FS) and a torque transducer traceable to NIST. Hematocrit was measured via centrifugation at ±1% HCT. Boundary condition uncertainty intervals were documented and used as inputs to the Monte Carlo UQ ensemble. Achieved level 4 meets the required level 4."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/output-comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
