      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/cou2/output-comparison",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria — MRL 5",
        "description": "Predicted hemolysis index must agree with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty bands at all five operating points; a formal validation metric (e.g. area validation metric or u-pooling) must be computed and reported; agreement must be demonstrated across the full operating envelope, not only at nominal conditions."
      },
      "rationale": "Predicted hemolysis index agrees with experiment within combined uncertainty at 4 of 5 operating points. At the highest flow-speed combination (6 L/min, 3600 RPM) the CFD prediction lies 12% outside the combined uncertainty band. The u-pooling validation metric is 0.74 (threshold ≥0.80 for level 5). Achieved level 4 is one gradation below the required level 5; this is the most consequential shortfall given that the COU requires absolute hemolysis prediction across the full envelope."
    },
    {
