        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria — MRL 5",
        "description": "The QoIs used in validation (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly mapped to the clinical endpoint (plasma-free hemoglobin rise rate); the mapping must be supported by published clinical or in-vitro evidence."
      },
      "rationale": "NIH is computed from plasma-free hemoglobin measurements using the ASTM F1841 protocol and is directly used in the regulatory hemolysis acceptance criterion. The mapping from NIH to chronic hemolysis risk is supported by published clinical data from VAD registries. Achieved level 4 meets the required level 4."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/relevance-validation-activities",
