      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/cou2/model-form",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — MRL 5",
        "description": "The turbulence model and hemolysis damage model must be selected based on a documented comparative study against at least two alternative model forms; the selected model must demonstrate superior predictive accuracy for the hemolysis QoI across the COU operating envelope; model-form uncertainty must be quantified and included in the total uncertainty budget."
      },
      "rationale": "A comparative study of three turbulence models (k-ω SST, realizable k-ε, and LES) and two hemolysis models (power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger and strain-based Bludszuweit) was conducted. The k-ω SST / power-law combination was selected based on best agreement at four of five operating points. Model-form uncertainty is estimated by the spread across model combinations but is reported as a range rather than a formal probability distribution, preventing full level 5 characterization. Achieved level 4."
    },
    {
