        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — MRL 5",
        "description": "All material properties and boundary conditions must be traceable to measured data with documented uncertainty; sensitivity of hemolysis QoI to each input must be ranked via a global sensitivity analysis (e.g. Sobol indices); high-sensitivity inputs must be characterized to tighter uncertainty bounds."
      },
      "rationale": "Sobol sensitivity indices were computed for eight model inputs (viscosity, density, inlet velocity profile, rotational speed, hematocrit, red blood cell fragility constant, turbulence intensity, and wall roughness). Viscosity and rotational speed are first-order dominant contributors. All inputs are characterized from calibrated measurements; high-sensitivity inputs have uncertainty bounds tightened to ±2% via repeated measurement. Achieved level 4 meets the required level 4."
    },
    {
