      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments use a standardized glycerol-saline blood analogue (ASTM F1841 protocol) rather than donor blood samples. Biological variability of donor blood is therefore not a source of experimental uncertainty in this validation campaign. This factor is scoped out because sample-to-sample biological variation is structurally absent from the experimental design; the analogue fluid properties are controlled to <0.5% batch-to-batch variation."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/equivalency-input-parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "The validation experiment and the COU simulation use identical pump geometry (FDA generic centrifugal pump, Rev 2.1 CAD), identical inlet and outlet boundary condition definitions, and identical rotational speed set-points. Input parameter equivalency is therefore exact by experimental design rather than requiring a formal equivalency argument. This factor is scoped out because there is no parameter mapping uncertainty to characterize; any residual geometric tolerance effect is bounded under the discretization error factor."
    }
